post_text:
SUTHERLAND PUBLIC SCHOOLS FOUNDATION SEEKING NOMINATIONS
The Sutherland Public Schools Foundation is seeking nominations of former Sutherland Public School Alumni who have excelled in areas of their life, including Education, Business, Humanitarian, Pursuits, Professional Field Accomplishments, The Arts, Athletics, Community Service, Service to Sutherland Public School and/or Sutherland Community, Service to Youth, Military, Heroism. Nomination forms, which include criteria that needs to be met, can be located on the Sutherland Public School website, www.spssailors.org , under the Foundation Tab. Questions regarding this award can be answered by any board member or Superintendent, Dan Keyser. Deadline for Nominations is February 1.

Nomination forms, which include criteria that needs to be met, can be located on the Sutherland Public School website, www.spssailors.org , under the Foundation Tab. Questions regarding this award can be answered by any board member or Superintendent, Dan Keyser. Deadline for Nominations is February 1.

post_text: Sutherland is a recipient of a early childhood education grant from the Nebraska Department of Education.
shared_text:
First Five Nebraska
June 5, 2015 at 5:00 PM ·

Congratulations to these school districts for receiving new Early Childhood Education grants today from the Nebraska Department of Education: Cambridge Public Schools, School District 145 – Waverly, Shelton Public Schools, Stapleton Public Schools, Sutherland Public Schools, Wausa Public Schools and Wayne Public Schools. We'd like to thank the Nebraska State Board of Education and NDE for their leadership in early childhood education, and for adopting revisions to Rule 11.
text:
Sutherland is a recipient of a early childhood education grant from the Nebraska Department of Education.

First Five Nebraska
June 5, 2015 at 5:00 PM ·

Congratulations to these school districts for receiving new Early Childhood Education grants today from the Nebraska Department of Education: Cambridge Public Schools, School District 145 – Waverly, Shelton Public Schools, Stapleton Public Schools, Sutherland Public Schools, Wausa Public Schools and Wayne Public Schools. We'd like to thank the Nebraska State Board of Education and NDE for their leadership in early childhood education, and for adopting revisions to Rule 11.
